                            <comment id="56829" author="adilger" created="Tue, 23 Apr 2013 16:55:06 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Fixed by &lt;a href=&quot;http://review.whamcloud.com/5247&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;http://review.whamcloud.com/5247&lt;/a&gt; in &lt;a href=&quot;https://jira.whamcloud.com/browse/LU-2733&quot; title=&quot;lustre-initialization-1: mgs_init0()) MGS: MGS filesystem method init failed: rc = -2&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;LU-2733&quot;&gt;&lt;del&gt;LU-2733&lt;/del&gt;&lt;/a&gt;.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="51875" author="utopiabound" created="Wed, 6 Feb 2013 12:47:06 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;This is related to but not caused by &lt;a href=&quot;https://jira.whamcloud.com/browse/LU-2749&quot; title=&quot;Test failure on test suite recovery-small: ost crash after test 29b causes test_53 to timeout&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;LU-2749&quot;&gt;&lt;del&gt;LU-2749&lt;/del&gt;&lt;/a&gt;.  The cause of this bug seems to be osd-zfs/osd_io.c::osd_oi_create() returning EEXIST to osd-zfs/osd_io.c::osd_find_or_add_seq on the OST, which causes the MDT to assume that the OST is further more insane.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
